OL,7,F"If you visited the farm and feel
OL,8,Funwell, please contact your GP or call
OL,9,FNHS 111. It is possible for this
OL,10,Finfection to be passed on from one
OL,11,Fperson to another. It is important to
OL,12,Fprotect yourself by washing your hands
OL,13,Fwell, particularly before preparing
OL,14,Ffood."
OL,16,FThe main symptoms of Cryptosporidium
OL,17,Finfection include:
OL,19,FSymptoms usually start two to 10 days
OL,20,Fafter contact with the parasite and
OL,21,Fcan last for up to two weeks.
